ASC.name: ASC
ASC.description: For Double-byte character set (DBCS) languages, the function changes full-width (double-byte) characters to half-width (single-byte) characters.

CHAR.name: CHAR
CHAR.description: Returns the character specified by the code number from the character set for your computer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a number between 1 and 255 specifying which character you want.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any worksheet information from which you want to remove nonprintable characters.

CODE.name: CODE
CODE.description: Returns a numeric code for the first character in a text string, in the character set used by your computer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text for which you want the code of the first character.

CONCATENATE.name: CONCATENATE
CONCATENATE.description: Joins several text strings into one text string.

DOLLAR.name: DOLLAR
DOLLAR.description: Converts a number to text, using currency format.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a number, a reference to a cell containing a number, or a formula that evaluates to a number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of digits to the right of the decimal point. The number is rounded as necessary; if omitted, Decimals = 2.

EXACT.name: EXACT
EXACT.description: Checks whether two text strings are exactly the same, and returns TRUE or FALSE. EXACT is case-sensitive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the first text string.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the second text string.

FIND.name: FIND
FIND.description: Returns the starting position of one text string within another text string. FIND is case-sensitive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text you want to find. Use double quotes (empty text) to match the first character in Within_text; wildcard characters not allowed.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the text containing the text you want to find.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Specifies the character at which to start the search. The first character in Within_text is character number 1. If omitted, Start_num = 1.

FINDB.name: FINDB
FINDB.description: Finds the specified substring (string-1) within a string (string-2) and is intended for languages the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

FIXED.name: FIXED
FIXED.description: Rounds a number to the specified number of decimals and returns the result as text with or without commas.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number you want to round and convert to text.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of digits to the right of the decimal point. If omitted, Decimals = 2.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a logical value: do not display commas in the returned text = TRUE; do display commas in the returned text = FALSE or omitted.

LEFT.name: LEFT
LEFT.description: Returns the specified number of characters from the start of a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text string containing the characters you want to extract.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Specifies how many characters you want LEFT to extract; 1 if omitted.

LEFTB.name: LEFTB
LEFTB.description: Extracts the substring from the specified string starting from the left character and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

LEN.name: LEN
LEN.description: Returns the number of characters in a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text whose length you want to find. Spaces count as characters.

LENB.name: LENB
LENB.description: Analyses the specified string and returns the number of characters it contains and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

LOWER.name: LOWER
LOWER.description: Converts all letters in a text string to lowercase.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text you want to convert to lowercase. Characters in Text that are not letters are not changed.

MID.name: MID
MID.description: Returns the characters from the middle of a text string, given a starting position and length.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text string from which you want to extract the characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the position of the first character you want to extract. The first character in Text is 1.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Specifies how many characters to return from Text.

MIDB.name: MIDB
MIDB.description: Extracts the characters from the specified string starting from any position and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

NUMBERVALUE.name: NUMBERVALUE
NUMBERVALUE.description: Converts text to number in a locale-independent manner.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the string representing the number you want to convert.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the character used as the decimal separator in the string.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the character used as the group separator in the string.

PROPER.name: PROPER
PROPER.description: Converts a text string to proper case; the first letter in each word to uppercase, and all other letters to lowercase.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is text enclosed in quotation marks, a formula that returns text, or a reference to a cell containing text to partially capitalize.

REPLACE.name: REPLACE
REPLACE.description: Replaces part of a text string with a different text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is text in which you want to replace some characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the position of the character in Old_text that you want to replace with New_text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of characters in Old_text that you want to replace.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the text that will replace characters in Old_text.

REPLACEB.name: REPLACEB
REPLACEB.description: Replaces a set of characters, based on the number of characters and the start position you specify, with a new set of characters and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

REPT.name: REPT
REPT.description: Repeats text a given number of times. Use REPT to fill a cell with a number of instances of a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text you want to repeat.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a positive number specifying the number of times to repeat text.

RIGHT.name: RIGHT
RIGHT.description: Returns the specified number of characters from the end of a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text string that contains the characters you want to extract.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Specifies how many characters you want to extract, 1 if omitted.

RIGHTB.name: RIGHTB
RIGHTB.description: Extracts a substring from a string starting from the right-most character, based on the specified number of characters and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

SEARCH.name: SEARCH
SEARCH.description: Returns the number of the character at which a specific character or text string is first found, reading left to right (not case-sensitive).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text you want to find. You can use the ? and * wildcard characters; use ~? and ~* to find the ? and * characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the text in which you want to search for Find_text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the character number in Within_text, counting from the left, at which you want to start searching. If omitted, 1 is used.

SEARCHB.name: SEARCHB
SEARCHB.description: Returns the location of the specified substring in a string and is intended for languages that use the double-byte character set (DBCS) like Japanese, Chinese, Korean etc..

SUBSTITUTE.name: SUBSTITUTE
SUBSTITUTE.description: Replaces existing text with new text in a text string.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text or the reference to a cell containing text in which you want to substitute characters.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the existing text you want to replace. If the case of Old_text does not match the case of text, SUBSTITUTE will not replace the text.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the text you want to replace Old_text with.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Specifies which occurrence of Old_text you want to replace. If omitted, every instance of Old_text is replaced.

T.name: T
T.description: Checks whether a value is text, and returns the text if it is, or returns double quotes (empty text) if it is not.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to test.

TEXT.name: TEXT
TEXT.description: Converts a value to text in a specific number format.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a number, a formula that evaluates to a numeric value, or a reference to a cell containing a numeric value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a number format in text form from the Category box on the Number tab in the Format Cells dialog box.

TRIM.name: TRIM
TRIM.description: Removes all spaces from a text string except for single spaces between words.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text from which you want spaces removed.

UNICHAR.name: UNICHAR
UNICHAR.description: Returns the Unicode character referenced by the given numeric value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the Unicode number representing a character.

UNICODE.name: UNICODE
UNICODE.description: Returns the number (code point) corresponding to the first character of the text.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the character that you want the Unicode value of.

UPPER.name: UPPER
UPPER.description: Converts a text string to all uppercase letters.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text you want converted to uppercase, a reference or a text string.

VALUE.name: VALUE
VALUE.description: Converts a text string that represents a number to a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text enclosed in quotation marks or a reference to a cell containing the text you want to convert.

AVEDEV.name: AVEDEV
AVEDEV.description: Returns the average of the absolute deviations of data points from their mean. Arguments can be numbers or names, arrays or references that contain numbers.

AVERAGE.name: AVERAGE
AVERAGE.description: Returns the average (arithmetic mean) of its arguments, which can be numbers or names, arrays or references that contain numbers.

AVERAGEA.name: AVERAGEA
AVERAGEA.description: Returns the average (arithmetic mean) of its arguments, evaluating text and FALSE in arguments as 0; TRUE evaluates as 1. Arguments can be numbers, names, arrays or references.

AVERAGEIF.name: AVERAGEIF
AVERAGEIF.description: Finds average (arithmetic mean) for the cells specified by a given condition or criteria.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the range of cells you want evaluated.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the condition or criteria in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be used to find the average.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Are the actual cells to be used to find the average. If omitted, the cells in range are used.

AVERAGEIFS.name: AVERAGEIFS
AVERAGEIFS.description: Finds average (arithmetic mean) for the cells specified by a given set of conditions or criteria.

BETADIST.name: BETADIST
BETADIST.description: Returns the cumulative beta probability density function.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value between A and B at which to evaluate the function.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is an optional lower bound to the interval of x. If omitted, A = 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is an optional upper bound to the interval of x. If omitted, B = 1.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value between A and B at which to evaluate the function.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: for the cumulative distribution function, use TRUE; for the probability density function, use FALSE.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is an optional lower bound to the interval of x. If omitted, A = 0.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is an optional upper bound to the interval of x. If omitted, B = 1.

BETA_INV.name: BETA_INV
BETA_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the cumulative beta probability density function (BETA.DIST).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the beta distribution.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is an optional lower bound to the interval of x. If omitted, A = 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is an optional upper bound to the interval of x. If omitted, B = 1.

BETAINV.name: BETAINV
BETAINV.description: Returns the inverse of the cumulative beta probability density function (BETADIST).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the beta distribution.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a parameter to the distribution and must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is an optional lower bound to the interval of x. If omitted, A = 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is an optional upper bound to the interval of x. If omitted, B = 1.

BINOMDIST.name: BINOMDIST
BINOMDIST.description: Returns the individual term binomial distribution probability.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number of successes in trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of independent trials.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the probability of success on each trial.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: for the cumulative distribution function, use TRUE; for the probability mass function, use FALSE.

BINOM_DIST.name: BINOM_DIST
BINOM_DIST.description: Returns the individual term binomial distribution probability.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number of successes in trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of independent trials.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the probability of success on each trial.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: for the cumulative distribution function, use TRUE; for the probability mass function, use FALSE.

BINOM_DIST_RANGE.name: BINOM_DIST_RANGE
BINOM_DIST_RANGE.description: Returns the probability of a trial result using a binomial distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number of independent trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the probability of success on each trial.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of successes in trials.

params.name: arg4
params.description: If provided this function returns the probability that the number of successful trials shall lie between number_s and number_s2.

BINOM_INV.name: BINOM_INV
BINOM_INV.description: Returns the smallest value for which the cumulative binomial distribution is greater than or equal to a criterion value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number of Bernoulli trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the probability of success on each trial, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the criterion value, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

CHIDIST.name: CHIDIST
CHIDIST.description: Returns the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which you want to evaluate the distribution, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHIINV.name: CHIINV
CHIINV.description: Returns the inverse of the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the chi-squared distribution, a value between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHISQ_DIST.name: CHISQ_DIST
CHISQ_DIST.description: Returns the left-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which you want to evaluate the distribution, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a logical value for the function to return: the cumulative distribution function = TRUE; the probability density function = FALSE.

CHISQ_DIST_RT.name: CHISQ_DIST_RT
CHISQ_DIST_RT.description: Returns the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which you want to evaluate the distribution, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHISQ_INV.name: CHISQ_INV
CHISQ_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the left-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the chi-squared distribution, a value between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHISQ_INV_RT.name: CHISQ_INV_RT
CHISQ_INV_RT.description: Returns the inverse of the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the chi-squared distribution, a value between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

CHITEST.name: CHITEST
CHITEST.description: Returns the test for independence: the value from the chi-squared distribution for the statistic and the appropriate degrees of freedom.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the range of data that contains observations to test against expected values.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the range of data that contains the ratio of the product of row totals and column totals to the grand total.

CONFIDENCE.name: CONFIDENCE
CONFIDENCE.description: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a normal distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the significance level used to compute the confidence level, a number greater than 0 and less than 1.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the population standard deviation for the data range and is assumed to be known. Standard_dev must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the sample size.

CONFIDENCE_NORM.name: CONFIDENCE_NORM
CONFIDENCE_NORM.description: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a normal distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the significance level used to compute the confidence level, a number greater than 0 and less than 1.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the population standard deviation for the data range and is assumed to be known. Standard_dev must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the sample size.

CONFIDENCE_T.name: CONFIDENCE_T
CONFIDENCE_T.description: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a Student's T distribution.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the significance level used to compute the confidence level, a number greater than 0 and less than 1.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the population standard deviation for the data range and is assumed to be known. Standard_dev must be greater than 0.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the sample size.

COUNT.name: COUNT
COUNT.description: Counts the number of cells in a range that contain numbers.

COUNTA.name: COUNTA
COUNTA.description: Counts the number of cells in a range that are not empty.

COUNTBLANK.name: COUNTBLANK
COUNTBLANK.description: Counts the number of empty cells in a specified range of cells.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the range from which you want to count the empty cells.

COUNTIF.name: COUNTIF
COUNTIF.description: Counts the number of cells within a range that meet the given condition.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the range of cells from which you want to count nonblank cells.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the condition in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be counted.

COUNTIFS.name: COUNTIFS
COUNTIFS.description: Counts the number of cells specified by a given set of conditions or criteria.

CRITBINOM.name: CRITBINOM
CRITBINOM.description: Returns the smallest value for which the cumulative binomial distribution is greater than or equal to a criterion value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number of Bernoulli trials.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the probability of success on each trial, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the criterion value, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

DEVSQ.name: DEVSQ
DEVSQ.description: Returns the sum of squares of deviations of data points from their sample mean.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value of the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the parameter value, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a logical value for the function to return: the cumulative distribution function = TRUE; the probability density function = FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value of the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the parameter value, a positive number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a logical value for the function to return: the cumulative distribution function = TRUE; the probability density function = FALSE.

F_DIST.name: F_DIST
F_DIST.description: Returns the (left-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which to evaluate the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value for the function to return: the cumulative distribution function = TRUE; the probability density function = FALSE.

FDIST.name: FDIST
FDIST.description: Returns the (right-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which to evaluate the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

F_DIST_RT.name: F_DIST_RT
F_DIST_RT.description: Returns the (right-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which to evaluate the function, a nonnegative number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

F_INV.name: F_INV
F_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the (left-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = F.DIST(x,...), then F.INV(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the F cumulative distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

FINV.name: FINV
FINV.description: Returns the inverse of the (right-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = FDIST(x,...), then FINV(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the F cumulative distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

F_INV_RT.name: F_INV_RT
F_INV_RT.description: Returns the inverse of the (right-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = F.DIST.RT(x,...), then F.INV.RT(p,...) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the F cumulative distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the numerator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the denominator degrees of freedom, a number between 1 and 10^10, excluding 10^10.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value for which you want the transformation, a number between -1 and 1, excluding -1 and 1.

FISHERINV.name: FISHERINV
FISHERINV.description: Returns the inverse of the Fisher transformation: if y = FISHER(x), then FISHERINV(y) = x.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value for which you want to perform the inverse of the transformation.

FORECAST_ETS.name: FORECAST_ETS
FORECAST_ETS.description: Returns the forecasted value for a specific future target date using exponential smoothing method..

FORECAST_ETS_CONFINT.description: Returns a confidence interval for the forecast value at the specified target date..

params.description: Is the data point for which Microsoft Excel predicts a value. It should carry on the pattern of values in the timeline..

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the array or range of numeric data you're predicting..

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the independent array or range of numeric data. The dates in the timeline must have a consistent step between them and can't be zero..

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a number between 0 and 1 that shows the confidence level for the calculated confidence interval. The default value is .95..

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is an optional numeric value that indicates the length of the seasonal pattern. The default value of 1 indicates seasonality is detected automatically..

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is an optional value for handling missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros..

FORECAST_ETS_SEASONALITY.name: FORECAST_ETS_SEASONALITY
FORECAST_ETS_SEASONALITY.description: Returns the length of the repetitive pattern an application detects for the specified time series..

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of numeric data you're predicting..

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the independent array or range of numeric data. The dates in the timeline must have a consistent step between them and can't be zero..

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is an optional value for handling missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros..

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is an optional numeric value for aggregating multiple values with the same time stamp. If blank, Microsoft Excel averages the values..

FORECAST_ETS_STAT.name: FORECAST_ETS_STAT
FORECAST_ETS_STAT.description: Returns the requested statistic for the forecast..

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of numeric data you're predicting..

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the independent array or range of numeric data. The dates in the timeline must have a consistent step between them and can't be zero..

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a number between 1 and 8, indicating which statistic Microsoft Excel will return for the calculated forecast..

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is an optional numeric value that indicates the length of the seasonal pattern. The default value of 1 indicates seasonality is detected automatically..

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is an optional value for handling missing values. The default value of 1 replaces missing values by interpolation, and 0 replaces them with zeros..

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is an optional numeric value for aggregating multiple values with the same time stamp. If blank, Microsoft Excel averages the values..

FREQUENCY.name: FREQUENCY
FREQUENCY.description: Calculates how often values occur within a range of values and then returns a vertical array of numbers that have one more element than Bins_array.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an array of or reference to a set of values for which you want to count frequencies (blanks and text are ignored).

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is an array of or reference to intervals into which you want to group the values in data_array.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value for which you want to calculate Gamma.

params.name: arg1

GAMMALN_PRECISE.description: Returns the natural logarithm of the gamma function.

GAUSS.name: GAUSS

GROWTH.name: GROWTH
GROWTH.description: Returns numbers in an exponential growth trend matching known data points.

params.description: Is the set of y-values you already know in the relationship y = b*m^x, an array or range of positive numbers.

HARMEAN.name: HARMEAN
HARMEAN.description: Returns the harmonic mean of a data set of positive numbers: the reciprocal of the arithmetic mean of reciprocals.

params.name: arg2

KURT.name: KURT
KURT.description: Returns the kurtosis of a data set.

LARGE.name: LARGE
LARGE.description: Returns the k-th largest value in a data set. For example, the fifth largest number.

params.name: arg1

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the position (from the largest) in the array or cell range of the value to return.

LINEST.name: LINEST
LINEST.description: Returns statistics that describe a linear trend matching known data points, by fitting a straight line using the least squares method.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the set of y-values you already know in the relationship y = mx + b.

params.name: arg2

params.name: arg3

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: return additional regression statistics = TRUE; return m-coefficients and the constant b = FALSE or omitted.

LOGEST.name: LOGEST
LOGEST.description: Returns statistics that describe an exponential curve matching known data points.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the set of y-values you already know in the relationship y = b*m^x.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is an optional set of x-values that you may already know in the relationship y = b*m^x.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a logical value: the constant b is calculated normally if Const = TRUE or omitted; b is set equal to 1 if Const = FALSE.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: return additional regression statistics = TRUE; return m-coefficients and the constant b = FALSE or omitted.

LOGINV.name: LOGINV
LOGINV.description: Returns the inverse of the lognormal cumulative distribution function of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with parameters Mean and Standard_dev.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability associated with the lognormal distribution, a number between 0 and 1, inclusive.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the standard deviation of ln(x), a positive number.

LOGNORM_DIST.name: LOGNORM_DIST
LOGNORM_DIST.description: Returns the lognormal distribution of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with parameters Mean and Standard_dev.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value at which to evaluate the function, a positive number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3

params.name: arg4

LOGNORM_INV.name: LOGNORM_INV

LOGNORMDIST.name: LOGNORMDIST

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the mean of ln(x).

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the standard deviation of ln(x), a positive number.

MAX.name: MAX

MAXA.name: MAXA
MAXA.description: Returns the largest value in a set of values. Does not ignore logical values and text.

MEDIAN.name: MEDIAN
MEDIAN.description: Returns the median, or the number in the middle of the set of given numbers.

MIN.name: MIN
MIN.description: Returns the smallest number in a set of values. Ignores logical values and text.

MINA.name: MINA
MINA.description: Returns the smallest value in a set of values. Does not ignore logical values and text.

NEGBINOMDIST.name: NEGBINOMDIST
NEGBINOMDIST.description: Returns the negative binomial distribution, the probability that there will be Number_f failures before the Number_s-th success, with Probability_s probability of a success.

NORMDIST.name: NORMDIST
NORMDIST.description: Returns the normal cumulative distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

params.description: Is the value for which you want the distribution.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the standard deviation of the distribution, a positive number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: for the cumulative distribution function, use TRUE; for the probability density function, use FALSE.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the arithmetic mean of the distribution.

params.name: arg3

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: for the cumulative distribution function, use TRUE; for the probability density function, use FALSE.

params.description: Is the value for which you want the distribution.

NORM_S_DIST.name: NORM_S_DIST
NORM_S_DIST.description: Returns the standard normal distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.description: Is the value for which you want the distribution.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a logical value for the function to return: the cumulative distribution function = TRUE; the probability density function = FALSE.

NORMSINV.description: Returns the inverse of the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability corresponding to the normal distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

NORM_S_INV.name: NORM_S_INV
NORM_S_INV.description: Returns the inverse of the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a probability corresponding to the normal distribution, a number between 0 and 1 inclusive.

PERCENTILE.name: PERCENTILE
PERCENTILE.description: Returns the k-th percentile of values in a range.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of data that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the percentile value that is between 0 through 1, inclusive.

PERCENTILE_EXC.name: PERCENTILE_EXC
PERCENTILE_EXC.description: Returns the k-th percentile of values in a range, where k is in the range 0..1, exclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of data that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the percentile value that is between 0 through 1, inclusive.

PERCENTILE_INC.name: PERCENTILE_INC
PERCENTILE_INC.description: Returns the k-th percentile of values in a range, where k is in the range 0..1, inclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of data that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the percentile value that is between 0 through 1, inclusive.

PERCENTRANK.name: PERCENTRANK
PERCENTRANK.description: Returns the rank of a value in a data set as a percentage of the data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of data with numeric values that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the value for which you want to know the rank.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is an optional value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage, three digits if omitted (0.xxx%).

PERCENTRANK_EXC.name: PERCENTRANK_EXC
PERCENTRANK_EXC.description: Returns the rank of a value in a data set as a percentage of the data set as a percentage (0..1, exclusive) of the data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or range of data with numeric values that defines relative standing.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the value for which you want to know the rank.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is an optional value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage, three digits if omitted (0.xxx%).

PERCENTRANK_INC.name: PERCENTRANK_INC
PERCENTRANK_INC.description: Returns the rank of a value in a data set as a percentage of the data set as a percentage (0..1, inclusive) of the data set.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the value for which you want to know the rank.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is an optional value that identifies the number of significant digits for the returned percentage, three digits if omitted (0.xxx%).

PERMUT.name: PERMUT
PERMUT.description: Returns the number of permutations for a given number of objects that can be selected from the total objects.

params.name: arg1

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of objects in each permutation.

PERMUTATIONA.name: PERMUTATIONA
PERMUTATIONA.description: Returns the number of permutations for a given number of objects (with repetitions) that can be selected from the total objects.

params.name: arg1

params.name: arg2

PHI.name: PHI
PHI.description: Returns the value of the density function for a standard normal distribution.

params.description: Is the number for which you want the density of the standard normal distribution.

params.description: Is the number of events.

QUARTILE.name: QUARTILE
QUARTILE.description: Returns the quartile of a data set.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or cell range of numeric values for which you want the quartile value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a number: minimum value = 0; 1st quartile = 1; median value = 2; 3rd quartile = 3; maximum value = 4.

QUARTILE_EXC.name: QUARTILE_EXC
QUARTILE_EXC.description: Returns the quartile of a data set, based on percentile values from 0..1, exclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or cell range of numeric values for which you want the quartile value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a number: minimum value = 0; 1st quartile = 1; median value = 2; 3rd quartile = 3; maximum value = 4.

QUARTILE_INC.name: QUARTILE_INC
QUARTILE_INC.description: Returns the quartile of a data set, based on percentile values from 0..1, inclusive.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the array or cell range of numeric values for which you want the quartile value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a number: minimum value = 0; 1st quartile = 1; median value = 2; 3rd quartile = 3; maximum value = 4.

RANK.name: RANK
RANK.description: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number for which you want to find the rank.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is an array of, or a reference to, a list of numbers. Nonnumeric values are ignored.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a number: rank in the list sorted descending = 0 or omitted; rank in the list sorted ascending = any nonzero value.

RANK_AVG.name: RANK_AVG
RANK_AVG.description: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list; if more than one value has the same rank, the average rank is returned.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number for which you want to find the rank.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is an array of, or a reference to, a list of numbers. Nonnumeric values are ignored.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a number: rank in the list sorted descending = 0 or omitted; rank in the list sorted ascending = any nonzero value.

RANK_EQ.name: RANK_EQ
RANK_EQ.description: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list; if more than one value has the same rank, the top rank of that set of values is returned.

params.description: Is the number for which you want to find the rank.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is an array of, or a reference to, a list of numbers. Nonnumeric values are ignored.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a number: rank in the list sorted descending = 0 or omitted; rank in the list sorted ascending = any nonzero value.

SKEW.name: SKEW
SKEW.description: Returns the skewness of a distribution: a characterisation of the degree of asymmetry of a distribution around its mean.

SKEW_P.name: SKEW_P
SKEW_P.description: Returns the skewness of a distribution based on a population: a characterisation of the degree of asymmetry of a distribution around its mean.

SMALL.name: SMALL
SMALL.description: Returns the k-th smallest value in a data set. For example, the fifth smallest number.

params.description: Is an array or range of numerical data for which you want to determine the k-th smallest value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the position (from the smallest) in the array or range of the value to return.

STANDARDIZE.name: STANDARDIZE
STANDARDIZE.description: Returns a normalised value from a distribution characterised by a mean and standard deviation.
