params.description: Is the present value.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the first period in the calculation.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the last period in the calculation.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the timing of the payment.

CUMPRINC.name: CUMPRINC
CUMPRINC.description: Returns the cumulative principal paid on a loan between two periods.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the total number of payment periods.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the present value.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the first period in the calculation.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the last period in the calculation.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the timing of the payment.

DB.name: DB
DB.description: Returns the depreciation of an asset for a specified period using the fixed-declining balance method.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the initial cost of the asset.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the salvage value at the end of the life of the asset.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of periods over which the asset is being depreciated (sometimes called the useful life of the asset).

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the period for which you want to calculate the depreciation. Period must use the same units as Life.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the number of months in the first year. If month is omitted, it is assumed to be 12.

DDB.name: DDB
DDB.description: Returns the depreciation of an asset for a specified period using the double-declining balance method or some other method you specify.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the initial cost of the asset.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the salvage value at the end of the life of the asset.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of periods over which the asset is being depreciated (sometimes called the useful life of the asset).

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the period for which you want to calculate the depreciation. Period must use the same units as Life.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the rate at which the balance declines. If Factor is omitted, it is assumed to be 2 (the double-declining balance method).

DISC.name: DISC
DISC.description: Returns the discount rate for a security.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's price per $100 face value.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

DOLLARDE.name: DOLLARDE
DOLLARDE.description: Converts a dollar price, expressed as a fraction, into a dollar price, expressed as a decimal number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a number expressed as a fraction.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the integer to use in the denominator of the fraction.

DOLLARFR.name: DOLLARFR
DOLLARFR.description: Converts a dollar price, expressed as a decimal number, into a dollar price, expressed as a fraction.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a decimal number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the integer to use in the denominator of a fraction.

DURATION.name: DURATION
DURATION.description: Returns the annual duration of a security with periodic interest payments.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's annual coupon rate.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's annual yield.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the nominal interest rate.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of compounding periods per year.

FV.name: FV
FV.description: Returns the future value of an investment based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the total number of payment periods in the investment.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the payment made each period; it cannot change over the life of the investment.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the present value, or the lump-sum amount that a series of future payments is worth now. If omitted, Pv = 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is a value representing the timing of payment: payment at the beginning of the period = 1; payment at the end of the period = 0 or omitted.

FVSCHEDULE.name: FVSCHEDULE
FVSCHEDULE.description: Returns the future value of an initial principal after applying a series of compound interest rates.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the present value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is an array of interest rates to apply.

INTRATE.name: INTRATE
INTRATE.description: Returns the interest rate for a fully invested security.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the amount invested in the security.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the amount to be received at maturity.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

IPMT.name: IPMT
IPMT.description: Returns the interest payment for a given period for an investment, based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the period for which you want to find the interest and must be in the range 1 to Nper.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the total number of payment periods in an investment.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the present value, or the lump-sum amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the future value, or a cash balance you want to attain after the last payment is made. If omitted, Fv = 0.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is a logical value representing the timing of payment: at the end of the period = 0 or omitted, at the beginning of the period = 1.

IRR.name: IRR
IRR.description: Returns the internal rate of return for a series of cash flows.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an array or a reference to cells that contain numbers for which you want to calculate the internal rate of return.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a number that you guess is close to the result of IRR; 0.1 (10 percent) if omitted.

ISPMT.name: ISPMT
ISPMT.description: Returns the interest paid during a specific period of an investment.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Interest rate per period. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Period for which you want to find the interest.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Number of payment periods in an investment.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Lump sum amount that a series of future payments is right now.

MDURATION.name: MDURATION
MDURATION.description: Returns the Macauley modified duration for a security with an assumed par value of $100.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's annual coupon rate.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's annual yield.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

MIRR.name: MIRR
MIRR.description: Returns the internal rate of return for a series of periodic cash flows, considering both cost of investment and interest on reinvestment of cash.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an array or a reference to cells that contain numbers that represent a series of payments (negative) and income (positive) at regular periods.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the interest rate you pay on the money used in the cash flows.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the interest rate you receive on the cash flows as you reinvest them.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the effective interest rate.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of compounding periods per year.

NPER.name: NPER
NPER.description: Returns the number of periods for an investment based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the payment made each period; it cannot change over the life of the investment.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the present value, or the lump-sum amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the future value, or a cash balance you want to attain after the last payment is made. If omitted, zero is used.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is a logical value: payment at the beginning of the period = 1; payment at the end of the period = 0 or omitted.

NPV.name: NPV
NPV.description: Returns the net present value of an investment based on a discount rate and a series of future payments (negative values) and income (positive values).

ODDFPRICE.name: ODDFPRICE
ODDFPRICE.description: Returns the price per $100 face value of a security with an odd first period.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's issue date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's first coupon date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's interest rate.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the security's annual yield.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg8
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg9
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

ODDFYIELD.name: ODDFYIELD
ODDFYIELD.description: Returns the yield of a security with an odd first period.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's issue date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's first coupon date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's interest rate.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the security's price.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg8
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg9
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

ODDLPRICE.name: ODDLPRICE
ODDLPRICE.description: Returns the price per $100 face value of a security with an odd last period.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's last coupon date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's interest rate.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's annual yield.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg8
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

ODDLYIELD.name: ODDLYIELD
ODDLYIELD.description: Returns the yield of a security with an odd last period.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's last coupon date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's interest rate.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's price.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg8
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

PDURATION.name: PDURATION
PDURATION.description: Returns the number of periods required by an investment to reach a specified value.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period..

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the present value of the investment.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the desired future value of the investment.

PMT.name: PMT
PMT.description: Calculates the payment for a loan based on constant payments and a constant interest rate.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period for the loan. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the total number of payments for the loan.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the present value: the total amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the future value, or a cash balance you want to attain after the last payment is made, 0 (zero) if omitted.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is a logical value: payment at the beginning of the period = 1; payment at the end of the period = 0 or omitted.

PPMT.name: PPMT
PPMT.description: Returns the payment on the principal for a given investment based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Specifies the period and must be in the range 1 to nper.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the total number of payment periods in an investment.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the present value: the total amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the future value, or cash balance you want to attain after the last payment is made.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is a logical value: payment at the beginning of the period = 1; payment at the end of the period = 0 or omitted.

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.description: Returns the price per $100 face value of a security that pays periodic interest.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's annual coupon rate.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's annual yield.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

PRICEDISC.name: PRICEDISC
PRICEDISC.description: Returns the price per $100 face value of a discounted security.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's discount rate.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

PRICEMAT.name: PRICEMAT
PRICEMAT.description: Returns the price per $100 face value of a security that pays interest at maturity.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's issue date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's interest rate at date of issue.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's annual yield.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

PV.name: PV
PV.description: Returns the present value of an investment: the total amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the interest rate per period. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the total number of payment periods in an investment.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the payment made each period and cannot change over the life of the investment.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the future value, or a cash balance you want to attain after the last payment is made.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is a logical value: payment at the beginning of the period = 1; payment at the end of the period = 0 or omitted.

RATE.name: RATE
RATE.description: Returns the interest rate per period of a loan or an investment. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the total number of payment periods for the loan or investment.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the payment made each period and cannot change over the life of the loan or investment.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the present value: the total amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the future value, or a cash balance you want to attain after the last payment is made. If omitted, uses Fv = 0.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is a logical value: payment at the beginning of the period = 1; payment at the end of the period = 0 or omitted.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is your guess for what the rate will be; if omitted, Guess = 0.1 (10 percent).

RECEIVED.name: RECEIVED
RECEIVED.description: Returns the amount received at maturity for a fully invested security.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the amount invested in the security.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's discount rate.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

RRI.name: RRI
RRI.description: Returns an equivalent interest rate for the growth of an investment.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number of periods for the investment.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the present value of the investment.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the future value of the investment.

SLN.name: SLN
SLN.description: Returns the straight-line depreciation of an asset for one period.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the initial cost of the asset.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the salvage value at the end of the life of the asset.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of periods over which the asset is being depreciated (sometimes called the useful life of the asset).

SYD.name: SYD
SYD.description: Returns the sum-of-years' digits depreciation of an asset for a specified period.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the initial cost of the asset.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the salvage value at the end of the life of the asset.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of periods over which the asset is being depreciated (sometimes called the useful life of the asset).

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the period and must use the same units as Life.

TBILLEQ.name: TBILLEQ
TBILLEQ.description: Returns the bond-equivalent yield for a treasury bill.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's discount rate.

TBILLPRICE.name: TBILLPRICE
TBILLPRICE.description: Returns the price per $100 face value for a treasury bill.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's discount rate.

TBILLYIELD.name: TBILLYIELD
TBILLYIELD.description: Returns the yield for a treasury bill.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the Treasury bill's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the Treasury Bill's price per $100 face value.

VDB.name: VDB
VDB.description: Returns the depreciation of an asset for any period you specify, including partial periods, using the double-declining balance method or some other method you specify.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the initial cost of the asset.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the salvage value at the end of the life of the asset.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the number of periods over which the asset is being depreciated (sometimes called the useful life of the asset).

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the starting period for which you want to calculate the depreciation, in the same units as Life.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the ending period for which you want to calculate the depreciation, in the same units as Life.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the rate at which the balance declines, 2 (double-declining balance) if omitted.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Switch to straight-line depreciation when depreciation is greater than the declining balance = FALSE or omitted; do not switch = TRUE.

XIRR.name: XIRR
XIRR.description: Returns the internal rate of return for a schedule of cash flows.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a series of cash flows that correspond to a schedule of payments in dates.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a schedule of payment dates that corresponds to the cash flow payments.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a number that you guess is close to the result of XIRR.

XNPV.name: XNPV
XNPV.description: Returns the net present value for a schedule of cash flows.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the discount rate to apply to the cash flows.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a series of cash flows that correspond to a schedule of payments in dates.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a schedule of payment dates that corresponds to the cash flow payments.

YIELD.name: YIELD
YIELD.description: Returns the yield on a security that pays periodic interest.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's annual coupon rate.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's price per $100 face value.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the number of coupon payments per year.

params.name: arg7
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

YIELDDISC.name: YIELDDISC
YIELDDISC.description: Returns the annual yield for a discounted security. For example, a treasury bill.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's price per $100 face value.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's redemption value per $100 face value.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

YIELDMAT.name: YIELDMAT
YIELDMAT.description: Returns the annual yield of a security that pays interest at maturity.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the security's settlement date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the security's maturity date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the security's issue date, expressed as a serial date number.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is the security's interest rate at date of issue.

params.name: arg5
params.description: Is the security's price per $100 face value.

params.name: arg6
params.description: Is the type of day count basis to use.

ABS.name: ABS
ABS.description: Returns the absolute value of a number, a number without its sign.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the real number for which you want the absolute value.

ACOS.name: ACOS
ACOS.description: Returns the arccosine of a number, in radians in the range 0 to Pi. The arccosine is the angle whose cosine is Number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the cosine of the angle you want and must be from -1 to 1.

ACOSH.name: ACOSH
ACOSH.description: Returns the inverse hyperbolic cosine of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number equal to or greater than 1.

ACOT.name: ACOT
ACOT.description: Returns the arccotangent of a number, in radians in the range 0 to Pi..

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the cotangent of the angle you want.

ACOTH.name: ACOTH
ACOTH.description: Returns the inverse hyperbolic cotangent of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the hyperbolic cotangent of the angle that you want.

AGGREGATE.name: AGGREGATE
AGGREGATE.description: Returns an aggregate in a list or database.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the Roman numeral you want to convert.

ASIN.name: ASIN
ASIN.description: Returns the arcsine of a number in radians, in the range -Pi/2 to Pi/2.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the sine of the angle you want and must be from -1 to 1.

ASINH.name: ASINH
ASINH.description: Returns the inverse hyperbolic sine of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number equal to or greater than 1.

ATAN.name: ATAN
ATAN.description: Returns the arctangent of a number in radians, in the range -Pi/2 to Pi/2.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the tangent of the angle you want.

ATAN2.name: ATAN2
ATAN2.description: Returns the arctangent of the specified x and y coordinates, in radians between -Pi and Pi, excluding -Pi.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the x-coordinate of the point.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the y-coordinate of the point.

ATANH.name: ATANH
ATANH.description: Returns the inverse hyperbolic tangent of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number between -1 and 1 excluding -1 and 1.

BASE.name: BASE
BASE.description: Converts a number into a text representation with the given radix (base).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number that you want to convert.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the base Radix that you want to convert the number into.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the minimum length of the returned string. If omitted leading zeros are not added.

CEILING.name: CEILING
CEILING.description: Rounds a number up, to the nearest multiple of significance.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to round.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the multiple to which you want to round.

CEILING_MATH.name: CEILING_MATH
CEILING_MATH.description: Rounds a number up, to the nearest integer or to the nearest multiple of significance.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to round.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the multiple to which you want to round.

params.name: arg3
params.description: When given and nonzero this function will round away from zero.

CEILING_PRECISE.name: CEILING_PRECISE
CEILING_PRECISE.description: Returns a number that is rounded up to the nearest integer or to the nearest multiple of significance.

COMBIN.name: COMBIN
COMBIN.description: Returns the number of combinations for a given number of items.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the total number of items.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of items in each combination.

COMBINA.name: COMBINA
COMBINA.description: Returns the number of combinations with repetitions for a given number of items.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the total number of items.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of items in each combination.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the cosine.

COSH.name: COSH
COSH.description: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the cotangent.

COTH.name: COTH
COTH.description: Returns the hyperbolic cotangent of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the hyperbolic cotangent.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the cosecant.

CSCH.name: CSCH
CSCH.description: Returns the hyperbolic cosecant of an angle.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the hyperbolic cosecant.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.description: Converts a text representation of a number in a given base into a decimal number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number that you want to convert.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the base Radix of the number you are converting.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians that you want to convert.

ECMA_CEILING.name: ECMA_CEILING
ECMA_CEILING.description: Rounds the number up to the nearest multiple of significance.

EVEN.name: EVEN
EVEN.description: Rounds a positive number up and negative number down to the nearest even integer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to round.

EXP.name: EXP
EXP.description: Returns e raised to the power of a given number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the exponent applied to the base e. The constant e equals 2.71828182845904, the base of the natural logarithm.

FACT.name: FACT
FACT.description: Returns the factorial of a number, equal to 123*...* Number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the nonnegative number you want the factorial of.

FACTDOUBLE.name: FACTDOUBLE
FACTDOUBLE.description: Returns the double factorial of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value for which to return the double factorial.

FLOOR.name: FLOOR
FLOOR.description: Rounds a number down to the nearest multiple of significance.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the numeric value you want to round.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the multiple to which you want to round. Number and Significance must either both be positive or both be negative.

FLOOR_PRECISE.name: FLOOR_PRECISE
FLOOR_PRECISE.description: Returns a number that is rounded down to the nearest integer or to the nearest multiple of significance.

FLOOR_MATH.name: FLOOR_MATH
FLOOR_MATH.description: Rounds a number down, to the nearest integer or to the nearest multiple of significance.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to round.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the multiple to which you want to round.

params.name: arg3
params.description: When given and nonzero this function will round towards zero.

INT.name: INT
INT.description: Rounds a number down to the nearest integer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the real number you want to round down to an integer.

ISO_CEILING.name: ISO_CEILING
ISO_CEILING.description: Returns a number that is rounded up to the nearest integer or to the nearest multiple of significance regardless of the sign of the number. However, if the number or the significance is zero, zero is returned..

LN.name: LN
LN.description: Returns the natural logarithm of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the positive real number for which you want the natural logarithm.

LOG.name: LOG
LOG.description: Returns the logarithm of a number to the base you specify.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the positive real number for which you want the logarithm.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the base of the logarithm; 10 if omitted.

LOG10.name: LOG10
LOG10.description: Returns the base-10 logarithm of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the positive real number for which you want the base-10 logarithm.

MOD.name: MOD
MOD.description: Returns the remainder after a number is divided by a divisor.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number for which you want to find the remainder after the division is performed.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number by which you want to divide Number.

MROUND.name: MROUND
MROUND.description: Returns a number rounded to the desired multiple.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to round.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the multiple to which you want to round number.

MULTINOMIAL.name: MULTINOMIAL
MULTINOMIAL.description: Returns the multinomial of a set of numbers.

MUNIT.name: MUNIT
MUNIT.description: Returns the unit matrix for the specified dimension.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an integer specifying the dimension of the unit matrix that you want to return.

ODD.name: ODD
ODD.description: Rounds a positive number up and negative number down to the nearest odd integer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to round.

PI.name: PI
PI.description: Returns the value of Pi, 3.14159265358979, accurate to 15 digits.

POWER.name: POWER
POWER.description: Returns the result of a number raised to a power.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the base number, any real number.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the exponent, to which the base number is raised.

PRODUCT.name: PRODUCT
PRODUCT.description: Multiplies all the numbers given as arguments.

QUOTIENT.name: QUOTIENT
QUOTIENT.description: Returns the integer portion of a division.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the dividend.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the divisor.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an angle in degrees that you want to convert.

RAND.name: RAND
RAND.description: Returns a random number greater than or equal to 0 and less than 1, evenly distributed (changes on recalculation).

RANDBETWEEN.name: RANDBETWEEN
RANDBETWEEN.description: Returns a random number between the numbers you specify.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the smallest integer RANDBETWEEN will return.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the largest integer RANDBETWEEN will return.

ROMAN.name: ROMAN
ROMAN.description: Converts an Arabic numeral to Roman, as text.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the Arabic numeral you want to convert.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number specifying the type of Roman numeral you want..

ROUND.name: ROUND
ROUND.description: Rounds a number to a specified number of digits.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number you want to round.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of digits to which you want to round. Negative rounds to the left of the decimal point; zero to the nearest integer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number that you want rounded down.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of digits to which you want to round. Negative rounds to the left of the decimal point; zero or omitted, to the nearest integer.

ROUNDUP.name: ROUNDUP
ROUNDUP.description: Rounds a number up, away from zero.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number that you want rounded up.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the number of digits to which you want to round. Negative rounds to the left of the decimal point; zero or omitted, to the nearest integer.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the secant.

SECH.name: SECH
SECH.description: Returns the hyperbolic secant of an angle.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the hyperbolic secant.

SERIESSUM.name: SERIESSUM
SERIESSUM.description: Returns the sum of a power series based on the formula.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the input value to the power series.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the initial power to which you want to raise x.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the step by which to increase n for each term in the series.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a set of coefficients by which each successive power of x is multiplied.

SIGN.name: SIGN
SIGN.description: Returns the sign of a number: 1 if the number is positive, zero if the number is zero, or -1 if the number is negative.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the sine. Degrees * PI()/180 = radians.

SINH.name: SINH
SINH.description: Returns the hyperbolic sine of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number.

SQRT.name: SQRT
SQRT.description: Returns the square root of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number for which you want the square root.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number by which p is multiplied.

SUBTOTAL.name: SUBTOTAL
SUBTOTAL.description: Returns a subtotal in a list or database.

SUM.name: SUM
SUM.description: Adds all the numbers in a range of cells.

SUMIF.name: SUMIF
SUMIF.description: Adds the cells specified by a given condition or criteria.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the range of cells you want evaluated.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the condition or criteria in the form of a number, expression, or text that defines which cells will be added.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Are the actual cells to sum. If omitted, the cells in range are used.

SUMIFS.name: SUMIFS
SUMIFS.description: Adds the cells specified by a given set of conditions or criteria.

SUMSQ.name: SUMSQ
SUMSQ.description: Returns the sum of the squares of the arguments. The arguments can be numbers, arrays, names or references to cells that contain numbers.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the angle in radians for which you want the tangent. Degrees * PI()/180 = radians.

TANH.name: TANH
TANH.description: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of a number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any real number.

TRUNC.name: TRUNC
TRUNC.description: Truncates a number to an integer by removing the decimal, or fractional, part of the number.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the number you want to truncate.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a number specifying the precision of the truncation, 0 (zero) if omitted.

CHOOSE.name: CHOOSE
CHOOSE.description: Chooses a value or action to perform from a list of values, based on an index number.

COLUMNS.name: COLUMNS
COLUMNS.description: Returns the number of columns in an array or reference.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an array or array formula, or a reference to a range of cells for which you want the number of columns.

HLOOKUP.name: HLOOKUP
HLOOKUP.description: Looks for a value in the top row of a table or array of values and returns the value in the same column from a row you specify.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to be found in the first row of the table and can be a value, a reference, or a text string.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a table of text, numbers, or logical values in which data is looked up. Table_array can be a reference to a range or a range name.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the row number in table_array from which the matching value should be returned. The first row of values in the table is row 1.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: to find the closest match in the top row (sorted in ascending order) = TRUE or omitted; find an exact match = FALSE.

HYPERLINK.name: HYPERLINK
HYPERLINK.description: Creates a shortcut or jump that opens a document stored on your hard drive, a network server, or on the Internet.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the text giving the path and file name to the document to be opened, a hard drive location, UNC address, or URL path.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is text or a number that is displayed in the cell. If omitted, the cell displays the Link_location text.

INDEX.name: INDEX
INDEX.description: Returns a value or reference of the cell at the intersection of a particular row and column, in a given range.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a range of cells or an array constant..

params.name: arg2
params.description: Selects the row in Array or Reference from which to return a value. If omitted, Column_num is required.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Selects the column in Array or Reference from which to return a value. If omitted, Row_num is required.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a reference to one or more cell ranges.

LOOKUP.name: LOOKUP
LOOKUP.description: Looks up a value either from a one-row or one-column range or from an array. Provided for backwards compatibility.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a value that LOOKUP searches for in Lookup_vector and can be a number, text, a logical value, or a name or reference to a value.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a range that contains only one row or one column of text, numbers, or logical values, placed in ascending order.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a range that contains only one row or column, the same size as Lookup_vector.

MATCH.name: MATCH
MATCH.description: Returns the relative position of an item in an array that matches a specified value in a specified order.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you use to find the value you want in the array, a number, text, or logical value, or a reference to one of these.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a contiguous range of cells containing possible lookup values, an array of values, or a reference to an array.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is a number 1, 0, or -1 indicating which value to return..

ROWS.name: ROWS
ROWS.description: Returns the number of rows in a reference or array.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is an array, an array formula, or a reference to a range of cells for which you want the number of rows.

TRANSPOSE.name: TRANSPOSE
TRANSPOSE.description: Converts a vertical range of cells to a horizontal range, or vice versa.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a range of cells on a worksheet or an array of values that you want to transpose.

VLOOKUP.name: VLOOKUP
VLOOKUP.description: Looks for a value in the leftmost column of a table and then returns a value in the same row from a column that you specify. By default, the table must be sorted in an ascending order.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to be found in the first column of the table, and can be a value, a reference, or a text string.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is a table of text, numbers, or logical values, in which data is retrieved. Table_array can be a reference to a range or a range name.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the column number in table_array from which the matching value should be returned. The first column of values in the table is column 1.

params.name: arg4
params.description: Is a logical value: to find the closest match in the first column (sorted in ascending order) = TRUE or omitted; find an exact match = FALSE.

ERROR_TYPE.name: ERROR_TYPE
ERROR_TYPE.description: Returns a number matching an error value..

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the error value for which you want the identifying number, and can be an actual error value or a reference to a cell containing an error value.

ISERR.name: ISERR
ISERR.description: Checks whether a value is an error other than #N/A, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

ISERROR.name: ISERROR
ISERROR.description: Checks whether a value is an error, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

ISEVEN.name: ISEVEN
ISEVEN.description: Returns TRUE if the number is even.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to test.

ISFORMULA.name: ISFORMULA
ISFORMULA.description: Checks whether a reference is to a cell containing a formula, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a reference to the cell you want to test. Reference can be a cell reference, a formula, or name that refers to a cell.

ISLOGICAL.name: ISLOGICAL
ISLOGICAL.description: Checks whether a value is a logical value (TRUE or FALSE), and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

ISNA.name: ISNA
ISNA.description: Checks whether a value is #N/A, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

ISNONTEXT.name: ISNONTEXT
ISNONTEXT.description: Checks whether a value is not text (blank cells are not text), and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want tested: a cell; a formula; or a name referring to a cell, formula, or value.

ISNUMBER.name: ISNUMBER
ISNUMBER.description: Checks whether a value is a number, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

ISODD.name: ISODD
ISODD.description: Returns TRUE if the number is odd.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value to test.

ISREF.name: ISREF
ISREF.description: Checks whether a value is a reference, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

ISTEXT.name: ISTEXT
ISTEXT.description: Checks whether a value is text, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want to test. Value can refer to a cell, a formula, or a name that refers to a cell, formula, or value.

N.name: N
N.description: Converts non-number value to a number, dates to serial numbers, TRUE to 1, anything else to 0 (zero).

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the value you want converted.

SHEET.name: SHEET
SHEET.description: Returns the sheet number of the referenced sheet.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is the name of a sheet or a reference that you want the sheet number of. If omitted the number of the sheet containing the function is returned.

SHEETS.name: SHEETS
SHEETS.description: Returns the number of sheets in a reference.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a reference for which you want to know the number of sheets it contains. If omitted the number of sheets in the workbook containing the function is returned.

TYPE.name: TYPE
TYPE.description: Returns an integer representing the data type of a value: number = 1; text = 2; logical value = 4; error value = 16; array = 64; compound data = 128.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Can be any value.

AND.name: AND
AND.description: Checks whether all arguments are TRUE, and returns TRUE if all arguments are TRUE.

IF.name: IF
IF.description: Checks whether a condition is met, and returns one value if TRUE, and another value if FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any value or expression that can be evaluated to TRUE or FALSE.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is the value that is returned if Logical_test is TRUE. If omitted, TRUE is returned. You can nest up to seven IF functions.

params.name: arg3
params.description: Is the value that is returned if Logical_test is FALSE. If omitted, FALSE is returned.

IFERROR.name: IFERROR
IFERROR.description: Returns value_if_error if expression is an error and the value of the expression itself otherwise.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any value or expression or reference.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is any value or expression or reference.

IFNA.name: IFNA
IFNA.description: Returns the value you specify if the expression resolves to #N/A, otherwise returns the result of the expression.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is any value or expression or reference.

params.name: arg2
params.description: Is any value or expression or reference.

NOT.name: NOT
NOT.description: Changes FALSE to TRUE, or TRUE to FALSE.

params.name: arg1
params.description: Is a value or expression that can be evaluated to TRUE or FALSE.

OR.name: OR
OR.description: Checks whether any of the arguments are TRUE, and returns TRUE or FALSE. Returns FALSE only if all arguments are FALSE.

XOR.name: XOR
XOR.description: Returns a logical 'Exclusive Or' of all arguments.
